	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64534065"><p>4th of July. Which means summer in the US. Fireworks can often be regulated because of wildfires in certain parts of the country. Consumer fireworks or industrial fireworks, same.</p><p>Because well, "fire". One dud going off in the distance can lead to a raging wildfire that then takes out a town because no one saw it and it was left to smoulder for a few hours.</p><p>Sometimes it doesn't take much, which is why permits and other things are often required.</p><p>And yes, stupid stunts abound - we saw what happened with drones<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

